text.__SUMMARY__: Quercus gomeziana is the accepted name of a tree species in the Asian sub-genus of 'ring-cupped oaks' and the family Fagaceae; there are no known subspecies.This oak tree grows in evergreen seasonal tropical forest, has large acorns in up to 50 mm cupules. and has been recorded from Vietnam (especially Lam Dong Province), where it may be called sồi Gomez.
